The 82G is a single-shot, 1-in-16 twist, Heavy Competition barrel (25") bolt action firearm. It was built to the standard of being sub-MOA rifles. It breaks like glass.

If you are looking to get into smallbore competitive shooting, this is simply the least expensive way to get in without dumping 1400 bucks into the lower-end anschutz rifles. 

This rifle is UNFIRED. It was bought as new (non-rusty) from the CMP when they still had these. The stock HAS NO CUT IN IT. This one was hand selected from the South Store in Anniston. title: For Sale:  Leupold VX-L 3.5-10x50mm Scope - Matte Black - Duplex - Mint w/ warranty
postcontent:
Up for sale is a like new Leopold VX-L scope. It is a 3.5-10x50mm in matte black with the duplex reticle. I put it on a Browning rifle of mine that never made it into the woods. Only ever shot it at the range one time to sight it in. Recently I sold the rifle, and no longer have use for the scope. Paid $899 for the scope, and it is in the same condition as it was the day I bought it. Lens is clear with zero imperfections. Tube of the scope is also mint. It is amazing to me how they make scopes with glass this clear.

For those unfamiliar with the VX-L it was designed to sit as low as possible on the barrel of your rifle without compromising the light gathering ability of a larger diameter scope. This scope gathers the same light as all other 50mm scopes, but it sits lower than even a 40mm scope does on your gun. When using it, it is like any other scope, you see a round circle out the end of it. The technology is truly amazing. 

Also, being that this is one of Leupold's top of the line scopes, it has the Gold-ring lifetime warranty offered by Leopold that is transferrable to anyone who owns the scope. If there is ever any problem with the scope, send it back, and they will replace it or fix it free of charge.

I have this same scope on my other two rifles, and I will never use any other scope besides this one. All of those people that have told me there is no benefit to this design are a testament to this as they now have all bought one for themselves. You won't be disappointed.

Please let me know if you have any questions. I will respond to emails quickly. I also have some pictures of it I can send upon request. Price is set at $600, but will also entertain reasonable offers. Thank you!

The High Wall is a wonderful rifle for those few who are up to the challenge of the single shot. Someone once said to beware of the man with a single shot rifle as he is likely to know how to shoot it.

This New In Box Uberti copy of the famous Winchester High Wall is outstanding in every detail. It's a handsome, no-nonsense rifle with beautiful casehardened colors on the receiver and lever, perfect bluing of the barrel, perfect wood, Winchester style rifle sights, and a wonderfully sweet trigger pull. title: For Sale:  THOMPSON - COLLECTORS - 10 MM CAL.- EXTRM. RARE! !LOW Production - Have YOU Ever Seen One?, CLASSIC!
postcontent: Go to London, Berlin, Bombay (sorry, Mumbai) or Ulan-Bator and show the image of a Thompson and you are likely to get two comments, America…..Chicago. When the good Colonel Thompson (later General) began to plan what became his masterpiece by founding the Auto-Ordinance Company nearly a century ago, little did he know that he was creating one of most iconic firearms and visual images in American history; the “Tommy Gun”, a.k.a. “Chicago Typewriter,” “Organ Grinder,” “Chopper,” and in the “Great War” parlance where its first use was originally intended, the “Trench Broom.” While Hollywood is largely responsible for establishing the “Tommy Gun” as a global image of prohibition era American gangsters, Thompson’s have established themselves in wars over a lifetime; from the jungles of Nicaragua in the Banana Wars to the killing alleys of post-communist Sarajevo. Modern imagery ranges from the anachronistic post-WWI retail advertisements of chap wearing cowboys to the inspirational lend-lease photos of Churchill’s inspection of costal defense troops complete with cigar, hat, suit and indomitable and defiant attitude. This Thompson Model 1927 A1 SEMI-AUTOMATIC rifle is chambered in 10 MM (yes, YOU read right), a VERY RARE caliber issue, PRODUCTION RUN reported to be 200 with majority retrofitted to .45 ACP (poor retail sales). Features finned barrel with Cutts compensator, pistol gripped fore-end, wood marts finished in a military oil finish walnut; matte black finish, adjustable rear sight, solid steel construction. I acquired this firearm at the liquidation of a collectors inventory in the 1990’s and it was professionally assessed NIB (new-in-box) condition with PAPERS showing slight handling marks, box and one stick magazine…..and has been safed ever since. Due to its RARITY OF CALIBER (how many have you SEEN?)and condition (NIB), this is ideal for any COLLECTOR who seeks to add what is, arguably THE most emblematic 20th Century AMERICAN image of firearms to their collection and one which should prove to be an INVESTMENT to appreciate over time

location: Surprise (loop 303 and bell rd), Phoenix, Arizona
postcontent:
PX4 Storm SubCompact: Big Tactical Performance, Concealable Size

The Beretta Px4 Storm SubCompact pistol is the most advanced deep concealment tactical pistol of its kind. It is a miniature-size version of the ultra-reliable PX4 Storm, a double/single-action pistol that keeps gaining an enthusiastic following among military and police organizations worldwide. The SubCompact does not sacrifice any of the features of its larger counterpart, while offering superior concealability and light weight.

Low Recoil in a Lightweight Package

In spite of its diminutive size, the Px4 Storm SubCompact was designed to be pleasant to shoot, offering minimal muzzle-jump and keeping recoil mild. The reason is that it is built around a rotating (or rotary) barrel system. The action dissipates much of the recoil radially, thereby reducing both the kick in the web of the shooting hand and the muzzle rise that happens at every shot. Besides being far less punishing on the hand than other handguns in its class, the PX4 SubCompact is quick back on target--a best-of-both-worlds situation combining superior concealment and low weight with a full-size shooting experience.

Superior Durability and Ease of Maintenance

The stainless steel barrel requires less maintenance and is corrosion- and sweat-resistant, making it perfectly suited for concealment even in hot and active conditions. This is a tactical pistol that is designed to work as hard as you while being as low-maintenance as possible. Disassembly is extremely easy and quick and requires no tools, while the tough and surface-treated steels enable you to keep it as good as new with a quick wipe even after a whole day in the holster.

User-Friendly, Feature-Rich and Ambidextrous

With the included interchangeable backstraps, the PX4 Storm SubCompact is easy and quick to adapt to different hand sizes (for instance, male or female) and grip styles. A built-in Picatinny rail further adds to its flexibility, making it possible to attach a variety of tactical accessories without any gunsmithing or alteration. Furthermore, most controls are either ambidextrous or reversible, making it easy to shoot and train with either hand dominant. Any shooter considering a reliable and soft-shooting subcompact for concealed carry or personal defense should give the PX4 SubCompact a very close look.
